# MCP Server â€” Firestorm AI Remote Control

The MCP (Model Context Protocol) server lets AI assistants (Claude
Desktop, and any other Streamable-HTTP MCP client) control this viewer
over a local, plain-HTTP JSON-RPC endpoint.

## Activation

1. Start the viewer.
2. Preferences â†’ **Network & Files** â†’ tab **"MCP Server"**.
3. Check "Enable MCP server", optionally set a custom port (default
   `13231`) and an auth token.
4. Restart the viewer. **Changes to this setting only take effect after
   a restart** â€” there is no live start/stop (see [Architecture](#architecture)).

A toast notification confirms the server is active each time it starts.

## Connection

The server listens on `http://127.0.0.1:<port>/mcp` (default port
`13231`) and speaks JSON-RPC 2.0 over plain HTTP â€” not HTTPS, and only
reachable from this machine.

### Claude Desktop

Claude Desktop's *Settings â†’ Connectors â†’ Add custom connector* dialog
requires an `https://` URL and will reject a local `http://` server.
Instead, edit `claude_desktop_config.json` directly (on Windows,
`%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json`) and restart Claude Desktop:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "firestorm": {
      "url": "http://127.0.0.1:13231/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

### Custom client (Python example)

```python
import httpx

resp = httpx.post("http://127.0.0.1:13231/mcp", json={
    "jsonrpc": "2.0", "method": "tools/list", "id": 1
})
print(resp.json())
```

## Available Tools

### Movement / interaction
| Tool | Parameters | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `avatar_sit` | `obj_uuid` or `position` {x,y,z} (optional) | Sits on the ground if neither given. Fire-and-forget. |
| `avatar_stand` | â€” | Fire-and-forget. |
| `avatar_walk_to` | `target_global` {x,y,z} (required), `stop_distance` | Autopilot; returns immediately, poll `get_position`. |
| `avatar_teleport` | `regionname` (required), `x`, `y`, `z` | Fire-and-forget. |
| `avatar_fly` | `enabled` (default true) | Returns resulting flying state. |

### Chat
| Tool | Parameters | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `chat_say` | `message` (required), `channel` (default 0) | 1s cooldown (shared with `chat_shout`). |
| `chat_shout` | `message` (required), `channel` (default 0) | Same cooldown as `chat_say`. |

### World / info
| Tool | Parameters | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `get_position` | â€” | Region + global position, region name. |
| `get_region_info` | â€” | Name, handle, origin, water height, maturity. |
| `get_nearby_agents` | `radius` (default 96m) | Nearby avatars: id, name, position, distance. |
| `list_nearby_objects` | â€” | Objects in view (id, name, owner, distance). Asynchronous (~3s); call again if some names are still missing. |

### Environment
| Tool | Parameters | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `get_environment` | â€” | Sun/moon azimuth+elevation (deg), cloud settings, haze/fog settings. |
| `set_environment` | `sun`, `moon` {azimuth, elevation}; `clouds` {color, scale, shadow, variance, scroll_x/y}; `haze` {density, horizon, blue_density, blue_horizon, distance_multiplier} | PATCH semantics â€” only given fields change. Applies instantly. |

### Social
| Tool | Parameters | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `list_friends` | â€” | Friends list: id, name, display name, online status. |
| `get_avatar_profile` | `avatar_id` (required) | About text, join date, partner, groups, picks, notes. Asynchronous (~15s timeout). |
| `set_avatar_notes` | `avatar_id`, `text` (required) | Overwrites profile notes (server-stored). Fire-and-forget. |
| `get_chat_history` | `avatar_id` (required), `max_lines` (default 200), `offset` (default: last page) | Reads the locally saved 1:1 IM transcript, paginated. Response has `total_messages`/`offset`/`returned`/`has_more` â€” page through the whole history via `offset=0`, then `offset += returned` while `has_more`. Passing `offset` loads the full transcript instead of just the recent tail, so paging can reach the entire history. |
| `send_im` | `avatar_id`, `message` (required) | Sends a 1:1 IM, creating the session if needed. Does not open the IM window. Asynchronous (~10s timeout resolving the avatar's name). |

### Inventory
| Tool | Parameters | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `inventory_list` | `folder_id` (default My Inventory root) | Direct subfolders + items of a folder. |
| `notecard_write` | `name`, `text` (required), `folder_id` (default Notecards folder) | Creates a new notecard. Asynchronous (~20s timeout: item creation + asset upload). |

Call `tools/list` for the full JSON schema of each tool.

## Security

- Disabled by default (`MCPServerEnabled = FALSE`).
- Binds to **127.0.0.1 only**, never `0.0.0.0`.
- Optional bearer token via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header,
  compared in constant time.
- Per-tool flood guard (min. 200ms between repeated calls to the same
  tool); `chat_say`/`chat_shout` additionally share a 1s cooldown.
- All requests are handled on the viewer's main thread (the same thread
  that runs the rest of the viewer) â€” no cross-thread synchronization
  needed, but also no request runs concurrently with anything else.
- A toast notification appears whenever the server starts, so it's hard
  to forget remote control is active for the session.

## Architecture

```
HTTP POST /mcp (127.0.0.1:<port>, JSON-RPC 2.0, plain text)
        â”‚
        â–Ľ
LLMCPHttpNode::post()            (llmcphttpnode.cpp)
        â”‚  auth check, JSON <-> LLSD (boost::json + llsdjson)
        â–Ľ
LLMCPToolRegistry::handleRequest (llmcptoolregistry.cpp)
        â”‚  JSON-RPC dispatch, rate limiting, tool lookup
        â–Ľ
Tool handler (llmcptools*.cpp)   - callback-based: most tools reply
        â”‚                          immediately; a few (get_avatar_profile,
        â”‚                          list_nearby_objects, notecard_write)
        â”‚                          complete later, after a network
        â”‚                          round-trip or a fixed settle time.
        â–Ľ
LLSD result -> JSON-RPC response -> back through LLMCPHttpNode
```

The HTTP transport is a small, purpose-built `LLChainIOFactory`/`LLSocket`
wrapper (not `LLIOHTTPServer::create()`, which crashes on a port conflict
and offers no way to stop a running listener) hung off the viewer's
existing `gServicePump`. It starts once at viewer launch if enabled -
there is intentionally no live stop/restart.

Where possible, tools bridge to event pumps the viewer already exposes
internally (`LLAgent` for movement, `LLChatBar` for chat, `LLInventory`
for inventory listing) rather than reimplementing viewer logic. See
[FEATURE_MCP.md](FEATURE_MCP.md) for the full design rationale and
per-phase implementation notes.

## Implementation

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `indra/newview/llmcphttpnode.h/.cpp` | HTTP transport, auth, server lifecycle. |
| `indra/newview/llmcptoolregistry.h/.cpp` | JSON-RPC dispatch, tool registry, rate limiting. |
| `indra/newview/llmcptools.cpp` | Movement, chat, and read-only core tools. |
| `indra/newview/llmcptoolssocial.cpp` | Profile, notes, chat history, friends list. |
| `indra/newview/llmcptoolsworld.cpp` | Nearby object listing. |
| `indra/newview/llmcptoolsenvironment.cpp` | Sky/environment read + patch. |
| `indra/newview/llmcptoolsinventory.cpp` | Inventory listing, notecard creation. |
| `indra/newview/skins/default/xui/en/panel_preferences_setup.xml` | Preferences UI (Network & Files â†’ MCP Server tab). |
| `indra/newview/app_settings/settings.xml` | `MCPServerEnabled`, `MCPServerPort`, `MCPServerAuthToken`. |

## MCP Protocol

The server implements JSON-RPC 2.0 with `initialize`, `ping`,
`tools/list`, and `tools/call`. Details:
https://modelcontextprotocol.io
